<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Scrabble Board Control Strategy</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Quiz · 2-letter words · Dictionary</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 7 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Every word you place either opens new scoring lanes or shuts them down. Board control — the art of manipulating available space — separates intermediate players from experts. Master this concept and you'll win games even when drawing mediocre tiles.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Board as a Battlefield</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triple Word Squares</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Double Word Squares</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Double Letter Squares</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triple Letter Squares</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The 15×15 Scrabble board has 61 premium squares. Controlling access to these — especially the 8 triple word scores — is the single most important positional skill you can develop.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When to Open the Board</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo-ready rack:</span> If your rack has good vowel/consonant balance with common letters (SATIRE, RETINA stems), open the board to create 7+ letter landing spots. The 50-point bonus rewards open play.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">When trailing:</span> If you're behind by 40+ points, you need big plays to catch up. Open boards create opportunities for high-scoring plays that can swing the game. Accept the risk — playing defensively while losing only cements the loss.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">How to open:</span> Extend words into empty board quadrants. Place words perpendicular to existing plays near edges. Leave vowels adjacent to premium squares that you plan to exploit next turn.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When to Close the Board</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Protecting a lead:</span> When ahead by 30+ points, restrict your opponent's options. Short parallel plays and board-edge words limit scoring opportunities without opening new lanes.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Opponent has bingo potential:</span> If they just exchanged and drew 7 fresh tiles, they likely have a strong rack. Close lanes to deny bingo placements — even sacrificing 10 points on your turn is worth blocking their 70+ point bingo.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">How to close:</span> Play parallel (stacking) alongside existing words. Use dead-end consonant clusters at board edges. Block squares adjacent to TWS with letters that are hard to hook.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
