<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Defensive Positional Plays</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Block TWS access</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play next to a TWS so no word can land on it. Even a 2-letter play here is high-value defence.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Dead-end lanes</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words ending at board edges with no extension possibilities. Your opponent can't build off them.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Open TWS lanes</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Never leave a clear path from an existing word to a TWS. That's handing your opponent a 3× multiplier.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Vowel gifts near TWS</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Vowels near premium squares make it easy for opponents to hook high-value plays onto them.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Net Impact Thinking</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A 15-point play that <span class="text-white font-medium">blocks your opponent's 45-point opportunity</span> has a net impact of +30 compared to a 25-point play that opens a TWS lane. Always evaluate moves by spread impact, not raw score alone.</p>
</div>

<p>Before placing any word, ask: "What does this give my opponent?" If your 30-point play opens a triple-triple possibility, the net impact might be negative. The best board controllers think two moves ahead — what will my opponent do, and what will that let me do next?</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Reading the Board State</h2>

<p>Experienced players scan the board before every turn using a mental checklist that guides whether to open or close:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Count open TWS lanes:</span> How many triple word squares are currently reachable in one play? If the answer is 2 or more, the board is dangerously open — consider closing unless you can exploit them first.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Check board edges:</span> Words extending to rows 1, 15 or columns A, O create access to corner TWS. If your opponent's last play moved toward an edge, they may be setting up a triple next turn.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Assess tile flow:</span> If 60+ tiles are played and no bingo has appeared, one is likely coming soon. Tighten the board pre-emptively to deny 7-letter landing spots.</p>
  </div>
</div>

